This paper focuses on the behavior planning of connected autonomous vehicles using deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also utilizes machine learning techniques such as deep learning and reinforcement learning, which are commonly found in the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a scalable state design and distributed learning algorithms, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
